  "riddle": "1. Seek the company that revolutionized transport under a blue oval, founded in what year?\n\n2. Within the annals of motor vehicles, how many distinct subsections are cataloged in the section dedicated to their essential components and design?\n\n3. From the number you discovered in clue 2, condense it to its digital root — what single digit remains?\n\n4. In the city known as the birthplace of an automotive titan, what is its elevation, as recorded in its descriptive box?\n\n5. To better understand this city's terrain, how high above sea level does it rise, as found in the geographical mapping?\n\n6. Close by, how many places of worship can be found in the vicinity of this city?\n\n7. Combine the elevation from clue 5 and the count of temples from clue 6 — what sum do you uncover?\n\n8. There exists a high-speed racing series adored worldwide; how many primary sections outline its Wikipedia details?\n\n9. What famed racing team, known for its speed and innovation, has how many language links listed at the top of its profile?\n\n10. The engine of a major auto conglomerate was set in motion on a specific date, what was the closing price of their stock on January 15, 2021?\n\n11. To continue your journey, find the next prime number after the value you just unearthed in clue 10.\n\n12. Look toward the iconic structure that resembles a wedge; how many institutions of higher learning are near its geographical coordinates?\n\n13. Calculate the value from clues 4 and 7 together: what remains when you sum them and take the result modulo 10? \n\nNow you have your final computation: what is the result of (750 + 242) % 10? Remember, your final answer should be a single digit, resting comfortably between 0 and 9.",
